text.__SUMMARY__: Acacia fagonioides is a shrub of the genus Acacia and the subgenus Pulchellae. It is native to an area in the Wheatbelt region of Western Australia.The spinescent shrub typically grows to a height of 0.2 to 0.6 metres (0.7 to 2.0 ft). It blooms from June to July and produces yellow flowers.
